Definition: the same as {{h3619}}; Kelub, the name of two Israelites; Chelub.
a form of {{h3612}}; Kelubai, an Israelite; Chelubai.
from {{h3615}}; completed; Keluhai, an Israelite; Chelluh.
denominative passive participle from {{h3618}}; bridehood (only in the plural); espousal.
from an unused root meaning to be complete; maturity; full (old) age.
the same as {{h3624}}; Kelach, a place in Assyria; Calah.
from {{h3605}} and {{h2374}}; every seer; Col-Chozeh, an Israelite; Col-hozeh.

from {{h3615}}; something prepared, i.e. any apparatus (as an implement, utensil, dress, vessel or weapon); armour(-bearer), artillery, bag, carriage,   furnish, furniture, instrument, jewel, that is made of, × one from another, that which pertaineth, pot,   psaltery, sack, stuff, thing, tool, vessel, ware, weapon,   whatsoever.
or כְּלוּא; from {{h3627}} (compare {{h3608}}); a prison; prison.
feminine of {{h3627}} (only in the plural); a kidney (as an essential organ); figuratively, the mind (as the interior self); kidneys, reins.
a primitive root; properly, to become pale, i.e. (by implication) to pine after; also to fear; (have) desire, be greedy, long, sore.
a primitive root; to address by an additional name; hence, to eulogize; give flattering titles, surname (himself).
from {{h3661}} in the sense of fastening; (from infixing its sting; used only in plural (and irregular in Exodus 8:17,18; Hebrews 13:14)); a gnat; lice, × manner.
from {{h3661}}; a plant (as set); × vineyard.
for {{h3641}}; Canneh, a place in Assyria; Canneh.

from {{h3559}}; properly, set upright; hence (figuratively as adjective) just; but usually (as adverb or conjunction) rightly or so (in various applications to manner, time and relation; often with other particles); after that (this, -ward, -wards), as... as,   (for-) asmuch as yet,   be (for which) cause,   following, howbeit, in (the) like (manner, -wise), × the more, right, (even) so, state, straightway, such (thing), surely,   there (where) -fore, this, thus, true, well, × you.
redupl. from {{h3648}}; obscuration (as if from shrinkage of light), i.e. an eclipse (only in plural); blackness.
the same as {{h3651}}, used as a noun; a stand, i.e. pedestal or station; base, estate, foot, office, place, well.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3651}}; so; thus.
for {{h3204}}; Conjah, an Israelite king; Coniah.
from a unused root meaning to twang; a harp; harp.
from an unused root meaning to store up or preserve; 'cummin' (from its use as a condiment); cummin.
a primitive root; to store away, i.e. (figuratively) in the memory; lay up in store.
or כָּמוֹ; a form of the prefix k, but used separately [compare {{h3651}}]; as, thus, so; according to, (such) as (it were, well as), in comparison of, like (as, to, unto), thus, when, worth.
or (Jeremiah 48:7) כְּמִישׁ; from an unused root meaning to subdue; the powerful; Kemosh, the god of the Moabites; Chemosh.
a primitive root; to pine after; long.
from {{h3642}}; pining; Kimham, an Israelite; Chimham.
from {{h3639}}; disgrace; shame.
or כַּלְנֵה; also כַּלְנוֹ; of foreign derivation; Calneh or Calno, a place in the Assyrian empire; Calneh, Calno. Compare {{h3656}}.
a primitive root; properly, to intertwine or contract, i.e. (by implication) to shrivel (as with heat); figuratively, to be deeply affected with passion (love or pity); be black, be kindled, yearn.
from {{h3648}}; properly, an ascetic (as if shrunk with self-maceration), i.e. an idolatrous priest (only in plural); Chemarims (idolatrous) priests.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3664}}; to assemble; gather together.

or כִּנֶּרֶתlemma כִּנֶרֶת missing dagesh, corrected to כִּנֶּרֶת; respectively plural and singular feminine from the same as {{h3658}}; perhaps harp-shaped; Kinneroth or Kinnereth, a place in Palestine; Chinnereth, Chinneroth, Cinneroth.

from {{h3670}}; an edge or extremity; specifically (of a bird or army) a wing, (of a garment or bedclothing) a flap, (of the earth) a quarter, (of a building) a pinnacle; bird, border, corner, end, feather(-ed), × flying,   (one an-) other, overspreading, × quarters, skirt, × sort, uttermost part, wing(-ed).
a primitive root; properly, to project laterally, i.e. probably (reflexive) to withdraw; be removed.
or כֶּסֶה; apparently from {{h3680}}; properly, fulness or the full moon, i.e. its festival; (time) appointed.
apparently a contraction for {{h3678}}, but probably by erroneous transcription for {{h5251}}; sworn.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3674}}; companion.
from {{h3655}}; a colleague (as having the same title); companion.
for {{h3778}}; Chaldean.
or כִּסֵּה; from {{h3680}}; properly, covered, i.e. a throne (as canopied); seat, stool, throne.
feminine of {{h3667}}; Kenaanah, the name of two Israelites; Chenaanah.

patrial from {{h3667}}; a Kenaanite or inhabitant of Kenaan; by implication, a pedlar (the Canaanites standing for their neighbors the Ishmaelites, who conducted mercantile caravans); Canaanite, merchant, trafficker.
a primitive root; to collect; hence, to enfold; gather (together), heap up, wrap self.
a primitive root; properly, to bend the knee; hence, to humiliate, vanquish; bring down (low), into subjection, under, humble (self), subdue.
from {{h3665}} in the sense of folding (compare {{h3664}}); a package; wares.
from {{h3665}}; humiliated; Kenaan, a son a Ham; also the country inhabited by him; Canaan, merchant, traffick.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3644}}; so or thus; so, (in) this manner (sort), thus.
a primitive root; to set out, i.e. plant; × vineyard.
from {{h3661}}; planted; Kenani, an Israelite; Chenani.
or כְּנַנְיָהוּ; from {{h3661}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has planted; Kenanjah, an Israelite; Chenaniah.
probably of foreign origin; Kisleu, the 9th Hebrew month; Chisleu.
feminine of {{h3689}}; in a good sense, trust; in a bad one, silliness; confidence, folly.
from {{h3688}}; fertile; Kesalon, a place in Palestine; Chesalon.
from {{h3688}}; hopeful; Kislon, an Israelite; Chislon.
a plural probably of foreign derivation; Casluchim, a people cognate to the Egyptians; Casluhim.
feminine plural of passive participle of {{h3688}}; fattened; Kesulloth, a place in Palestine; Chesulloth.
a primitive root; to shear; × only, poll. Compare {{h3765}}.
from the feminine plural of {{h3689}} and {{h8396}}; flanks of Tabor; Kisloth-Tabor, a place in Palestine; Chisloth-tabor.
a primitive root; to estimate; make count.
from {{h3697}}; spelt (from its bristliness as if just shorn); fitches, rie.
from the same as {{h3611}}; a bird-trap (as furnished with a clap-stick or treadle to spring it); hence, a basket (as resembling a wicker cage); basket, cage.
from {{h3634}}; a bride (as if perfect); hence, a son's wife; bride, daughter-in-law, spouse.
from an unused root means. to yelp, or else to attack; a dog; hence (by euphemism) a male prostitute; dog.
dual of {{h3608}} in the original sense of separation; two heterogeneities; divers seeds (-e kinds), mingled (seed).
from {{h3612}} and {{h672}}; Caleb-Ephrathah, a place in Egypt (if the text is correct); Caleb-ephrathah.
perhaps a form of {{h3611}}, or else from the same root in the sense of forcible; Caleb, the name of three Israelites; Caleb.

a primitive root; to end, whether intransitive (to cease, be finished, perish) or transitive (to complete, prepare, consume); accomplish, cease, consume (away), determine, destroy (utterly), be (when... were) done, (be an) end (of), expire, (cause to) fail, faint, finish, fulfil, × fully, × have, leave (off), long, bring to pass, wholly reap, make clean riddance, spend, quite take away, waste.
probably by erroneous transcription for כָּלֵבִי; patronymically from {{h3612}}; a Calebite or descendant of Caleb; of the house of Caleb.
from {{h3615}}; a completion; adverb, completely; also destruction; altogether, (be, utterly) consume(-d), consummation(-ption), was determined, (full, utter) end, riddance.
from {{h3615}}; pining; fail.
from {{h3680}}; a cover (garment); figuratively, a veiling; covering, raiment, vesture.
a primitive root; to cut off; cut down (up).

a primitive root; properly, to plump, i.e. fill up hollows; by implication, to cover (for clothing or secrecy); clad self, close, clothe, conceal, cover (self), (flee to) hide, overwhelm. Compare {{h3780}}.
passive participle of {{h3680}}; properly, covered, i.e. (as noun) a covering; covering.
the same as {{h3684}}; Kesil, a place in Palestine; Chesil.
from {{h3684}}; silliness; foolish.
from {{h3688}}; properly, fat, i.e. (figuratively) stupid or silly; fool(-ish).
the same as {{h3684}}; any notable constellation; specifically Orion (as if a burly one); constellation, Orion.
a primitive root; properly, to be fat, i.e. (figuratively) silly; be foolish.

from {{h3688}}; properly, fatness, i.e. by implication (literally) the loin (as the seat of the leaf fat) or (generally) the viscera; also (figuratively) silliness or (in a good sense) trust; confidence, flank, folly, hope, loin.
from {{h3607}}; a prison; prison. Compare {{h3610}}, {{h3628}}.
apparently from {{h3607}} and {{h1}}; restraint of (his) father; Kilab, an Israelite; Chileab.
from {{h3541}}; just so, referring to the previous or following context; after that (this) manner, this matter, (even) so, in such a case, thus.

from {{h3769}}; a circle, i.e. (by implication) a circumjacent tract or region, especially the Ghor or valley of the Jordan; also a (round) loaf; also a talent (or large [round] coin); loaf, morsel, piece, plain, talent.
from {{h3787}}; compare {{h6418}}; literally a director, i.e. the spindle or shank of a distaff, by which it is twirled; spindle.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3605}}; all, any,   (forasmuch) as,   be-(for this) cause, every,   no (manner, -ne),   there (where) -fore,   though, what (where, who) -soever, (the) whole.
a primitive root; to restrict, by act (hold back or in) or word (prohibit); finish, forbid, keep (back), refrain, restrain, retain, shut up, be stayed, withhold.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3603}}; a talent; talent.

or (Jeremiah 33:8) כּוֹל; from {{h3634}}; properly, the whole; hence, all, any or every (in the singular only, but often in a plural sense); (in) all (manner, (ye)), altogether, any (manner), enough, every (one, place, thing), howsoever, as many as, (no-) thing, ought, whatsoever, (the) whole, whoso(-ever).
a primitive root; properly, to wound; but only figuratively, to taunt or insult; be (make) ashamed, blush, be confounded, be put to confusion, hurt, reproach, (do, put to) shame.
from {{h3634}}; complete; Kelal, an Israelite; Chelal.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3634}}; to complete; finish, make (set) up.
a primitive root; to complete; (make) perfect.
from {{h3557}}; sustenance; Calcol, an Israelite; Calcol, Chalcol.
from {{h3634}}; complete; as noun, the whole (specifically, a sacrifice entirely consumed); as adverb, fully; all, every whit, flame, perfect(-ion), utterly, whole burnt offering (sacrifice), wholly.
from {{h3615}}; pining, destruction; consumption, failing.
a form of {{h3631}}; Kiljon, an Israelite; Chilion.
from {{h3637}}; disgrace; confusion, dishonour, reproach, shame.
of foreign derivation; Kilmad, a place apparently in the Assyrian empire; Chilmad.
